OL,3,C'We shouldn't have to fight for an
OL,4,Ceducation for our son because he's got
OL,5,CALN'
OL,7,FParents of a four-year-old boy with
OL,8,Fadditional learning needs say their
OL,9,Ffight to get him a place in a special
OL,10,Fschool was "one of the most
OL,11,Fchallenging times" of their lives.
OL,13,FChloe and Craig Boulton, from
OL,14,FAberdare, refused to put their son
OL,15,FGabriel, who is autistic, into
OL,16,Fmainstream school as they felt a lack
OL,17,Fof specialised provision could have
OL,18,Fcaused him to regress.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/13
