OL,3,C'We shouldn't have to fight for an
OL,4,Ceducation for our son because he's got
OL,5,CALN'
OL,7,FInstead, they paid for him to attend
OL,8,Ftwo private creches for a year while
OL,9,Fhis place at a special school was
OL,10,Ffinalised after his Individual
OL,11,FDevelopment Plan (IDP) was completed,
OL,12,Fa process the family claim was "too
OL,13,Flong-winded".
OL,15,FEvery child who is identified as
OL,16,Fhaving ALN by a Welsh local authority
OL,17,Fmust have a statutory IDP which should
OL,18,Finclude additional learning provision
OL,19,F(ALP) agreed by health services,
OL,20,Fsocial services and other services,
OL,21,Fincluding education.
