OL,3,C'We shouldn't have to fight for an
OL,4,Ceducation for our son because he's got
OL,5,CALN'
OL,7,F"They said we needed to put his name
OL,8,Fdown for a mainstream education
OL,9,Fprovision, but as his carers we felt
OL,10,Fthat wouldn't be meeting his needs and
OL,11,Fhe would actually regress.
OL,13,F"So we decided to pay privately for
OL,14,Four own education provision in two
OL,15,Fcreche settings, and kept him out (of
OL,16,Fschool) for a year. He missed a year,
OL,17,Fwhere other neurotypical children who
OL,18,Fwent to school with all their other
OL,19,Ffriends.
