OL,3,C'We shouldn't have to fight for an
OL,4,Ceducation for our son because he's got
OL,5,CALN'
OL,7,F"For that year, he should have been in
OL,8,Fa provision. Because of his additional
OL,9,Fneeds, we had to wait.
OL,11,F"He couldn't go into that mainstream
OL,12,Fsetting. It would have set him back.
OL,13,FIt would have been dangerous,
OL,14,Factually. It's not fair on him or the
OL,15,Fclass teacher."
OL,17,FGabriel started school in September
OL,18,F2023 when he was aged four.
