OL,3,C'We shouldn't have to fight for an
OL,4,Ceducation for our son because he's got
OL,5,CALN'
OL,7,F"He's where he needs to be now but
OL,8,Fthat hasn't come without probably the
OL,9,Fworst two years of my life," Chloe
OL,10,Fsaid.
OL,12,F"He's happy going to school, he's
OL,13,Fsaying a few words. They're baby
OL,14,Fsteps, but they're all steps in the
OL,15,Fright direction. They are a fantastic
OL,16,Fprovision, the teachers go above and
OL,17,Fbeyond, we've seen such progress in
OL,18,Fhim.
