OL,3,C'We shouldn't have to fight for an
OL,4,Ceducation for our son because he's got
OL,5,CALN'
OL,7,F"He's lovely, he's funny, happy, very
OL,8,Fplacid, he's got lovely, lovely ways,
OL,9,Fhe's an absolute pleasure to be around
OL,10,Fand we're so proud of him as his
OL,11,Fparents. Even though we have our
OL,12,Fchallenges with him, I wouldn't change
OL,13,FGabriel for the world. He is our blue-
OL,14,Feyed boy, he's beautiful."
OL,16,FChloe and Craig say the wait for his
OL,17,Fautism diagnosis was also far too long.
OL,19,F"He actually got into a special school
OL,20,Fbefore we even had a diagnosis of
OL,21,Fautism," Chloe said.
