OL,3,C'We shouldn't have to fight for an
OL,4,Ceducation for our son because he's got
OL,5,CALN'
OL,7,F"Although it was difficult, we were
OL,8,Fquite fortunate because of the
OL,9,Fflexibility I had in my job - I run my
OL,10,Fown business. But most people haven't
OL,11,Fgot that luxury.
OL,13,F"He is in the right place. As hard as
OL,14,Fit is, the journey was worth it."
OL,16,FA spokesperson for Rhondda Cynon Taf
OL,17,FCouncil said: "Our policy is that all
OL,18,Flearners, as far as possible, should
OL,19,Fbe educated in mainstream schools with
OL,20,Fsupport provided in these settings
OL,21,Fwhere necessary.
